docs.abstract: Mayor Buttigieg said Senator Warren  had not been forthcoming about whether she would raise taxes on the middle class to help finance a health care plan.
docs.snippet: Mayor Buttigieg said Senator Warren  had not been forthcoming about whether she would raise taxes on the middle class to help finance a health care plan.
docs.lead_paragraph: Pete Buttigieg directly criticized Elizabeth Warren over health care at Tuesday night’s debate, saying that she had not been forthcoming about whether she would raise taxes on the middle class to help finance “Medicare for all.”

headline.main: ‘Medicare for All’: Elizabeth Warren and Pete Buttigieg Clash at Debate

docs.abstract: How does a place that celebrates its own border-crossing heritage understand President Trump and a rallying cry of “send her back”?
docs.snippet: How does a place that celebrates its own border-crossing heritage understand President Trump and a rallying cry of “send her back”?
docs.lead_paragraph: OLDENBURG, Ind. — The last time President Trump held a rally, and his supporters shouted a deafening chorus of “Send her back,” the Franciscan Sisters of Oldenburg were outraged. Some of them called the chant, and remarks the president has made about immigrants, “racist,” “terrible” and “disgusting.”

headline.main: This Red-State Town Loves Immigrant Stories. Some of Them, Anyway.
headline.print_headline: Deep in Trump Country, Nuns Resist With Appeal  To Heritage: ‘Immigrants and Refugees Welcome’

docs.abstract: Facing a backlash, Mr. Buttigieg’s campaign distanced itself from a lawyer, Steve Patton, who tried to block the release of a video of the police killing of a black teenager. Mr. Patton was set to co-host a fund-raiser for Mr. Buttigieg.
docs.snippet: Facing a backlash, Mr. Buttigieg’s campaign distanced itself from a lawyer, Steve Patton, who tried to block the release of a video of the police killing of a black teenager. Mr. Patton was set to co-host a fund-raiser for Mr. Buttigieg.
docs.lead_paragraph: Pete Buttigieg’s presidential campaign, facing criticism, distanced itself on Friday from a Chicago lawyer who tried to block the release of footage of the 2014 police shooting of a black teenager, Laquan McDonald.

headline.main: Pete Buttigieg Cuts Ties With Donor Linked to Laquan McDonald Cover-Up

docs.lead_paragraph: The advertisement began with a photo of Representative Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez bursting into flames, followed by a black-and-white image of skulls lined up on the ground.

headline.main: Elizabeth Heng Ad, Targeting Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez, Draws a Backlash

docs.abstract: One day after President Trump hailed his own record on criminal justice and belittled Barack Obama’s, Democrats hit back at his record and history of racial demagogy.
docs.snippet: One day after President Trump hailed his own record on criminal justice and belittled Barack Obama’s, Democrats hit back at his record and history of racial demagogy.
docs.lead_paragraph: COLUMBIA, S.C. — One day after President Trump claimed he had done more for black voters than the Obama administration had, several Democratic presidential candidates spoke at the same historically black college on Saturday and issued a blistering rebuke of both the president and the event’s organizers — whom they accused of giving Mr. Trump an undeserved platform.

headline.main: Democratic Candidates Rebuke Trump at Criminal Justice Forum
headline.print_headline: Candidates Rebuke Trump At Criminal Justice Forum

docs.abstract: The criticism of Elizabeth Warren illustrated her status as an emerging front-runner, while Joe Biden faced scrutiny over his son’s financial dealings overseas.
docs.snippet: The criticism of Elizabeth Warren illustrated her status as an emerging front-runner, while Joe Biden faced scrutiny over his son’s financial dealings overseas.
docs.lead_paragraph: WESTERVILLE, Ohio — Senator Elizabeth Warren of Massachusetts faced a sustained barrage of criticism from her Democratic rivals at a presidential debate in Ohio on Tuesday, tangling with a group of underdog moderates who assailed her liberal economic proposals, while former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. appeared to fade from the fray after parrying President Trump’s attacks on his family.

headline.main: Warren Draws Fire From All Sides, Reflecting a Shift in Fortunes in Race
headline.print_headline: Warren Defends  Her Health Plan  As Rivals Pounce

byline.original: By Alexander Burns and Jonathan Martin

docs.abstract: Beto O’Rourke took aim at Elizabeth Warren, who wants to create an annual tax on the accumulated wealth of the richest Americans.
docs.snippet: Beto O’Rourke took aim at Elizabeth Warren, who wants to create an annual tax on the accumulated wealth of the richest Americans.
docs.lead_paragraph: Former Representative Beto O’Rourke suggested at Tuesday night’s debate that Senator Elizabeth Warren was being “punitive” as she argues for a tax on the wealth of the richest Americans, a proposal that is a centerpiece of her presidential campaign.

headline.main: O’Rourke Says Warren Is Being ‘Punitive’ as She Pitches a Wealth Tax

docs.abstract: The actress is trying to stay just famous enough to still get invited to Washington.
docs.snippet: The actress is trying to stay just famous enough to still get invited to Washington.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Alyssa Milano was on Capitol Hill in a floral dress and black Dr. Martens combat boots, her hair pulled into a tight bun atop her head. This is the look — the bun and the boots — that her best friend, Alaa Khaled, says signals to him that “we’re in for something.”

headline.main: Alyssa Milano, Celebrity Activist for the Celebrity Presidential Age
